# No Hardcoded Strings or Colors

## Strings — Zero Tolerance for Magic Strings

**Every** user-facing string must be a constant in `internal/constants/`. Never inline text in views, components, or app.go.

All magic strings are centralized in `internal/constants/`:
- **`constants.go`**: URLs, version, package specs, file names, directory names, struct types
- **`strings.go`**: UI copy — step names, tab labels, placeholders, button labels, help text, status labels, phase names

```go
// BAD — hardcoded string in a view
banner := styles.SuccessText.Render("Analysis Complete")

// GOOD — use a constant
banner := styles.SuccessText.Render(constants.ResultsBanner)
```

Naming prefixes: `TabXxx`, `StepNameXxx`, `ButtonXxx`, `HelpKeyXxx`, `HelpDescXxx`, `PhaseXxx`, `XxxFile`, `PlaceholderXxx`

## Colors — Always Use Global Style Variables

**Never** hardcode hex colors, ANSI codes, or `lipgloss.Color()` in views or components. Always use the variables from `internal/tui/styles/`.

```go
// BAD — hardcoded color
lipgloss.NewStyle().Foreground(lipgloss.Color("#FEC089"))

// GOOD — use style variable
lipgloss.NewStyle().Foreground(styles.BoldTextColor)

// GOOD — use pre-built style
styles.Accent.Render("highlighted text")
```

Available color variables: `TextColor`, `BoldTextColor`, `MutedColor`, `ErrorColor`, `SuccessColor`, `WarningColor`, `SpinnerColor`, `InvertedTextColor`

Available pre-built styles: `Title`, `Subtitle`, `Body`, `Muted`, `Accent`, `Error`, `SuccessText`, `Label`, `Value`, `Box`, `BoxActive`, `Button`, `ButtonActive`, `TabActive`, `TabInactive`, `ListItem`, `ListItemSelected`, etc.

## Adding New Constants
1. Determine if it's a UI string (→ `strings.go`) or a technical value (→ `constants.go`)
2. Follow the existing naming prefix convention
3. Group with related constants using the existing `const ( ... )` blocks
